race.comment: EVER WAS (1) recorded a strong on-speed win first up over this journey at Nowra. He will be better for that, and the go-to jockey around these parts is engaged. Looks the testing material again. SEEKING PROPHET (8) settled well back last start over 2000m at Canberra and was beaten easily. She'd won at the non-TABs prior, following a switch from a Victorian yard. Much better suited back to a mile, and her Mornington run over this trip three back stacks up. SAPPHIRES SON (4) is in a strong local stable and races best this course/distance. Has the handy 3kg claim and a much sharper effort is likely. BEOGRAD BOY (5) is hard to catch but has the ability, and he can get into the money in a weak lineup. ZARTAMAY (3) drips back from the mile off a 50 win at Mudgee in a non-TAB and with a 3kg claim will be around the mark.
